//Fracture - Fibula proximal AO 4F1


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Fracture - Fibula proximal AO 4F1' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And '4F1A: Simple fracture' radio button is enabled
And '4F1B: Multifragmentary fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Fracture older, consolidated' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspicion of' radio button is enabled

When I select '4F1A: Simple fracture' radio button
Then 'n: Extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And 'o: Complete articular' radio button is enabled

When I select '4F1B: Multifragmentary fracture' radio button
Then 'n: Extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And 'o: Complete articular' radio button is enabled
